●	The design successfully demonstrates that wide fan-in domino logic is feasible in sub-threshold mode, suitable for low power, moderate speed applications. 
●	Compared to static CMOS, the domino logic shows competitive power benefits but at the cost of higher delay, typical for this regime. 
●	The results align with literature indicating that adaptive sub-threshold voltage control in domino logic reduces power dissipation and improves noise immunity, especially for wide fan-in gates. 
●	This work confirms that the sub-threshold domino approach is robust for ultra-low power VLSI designs, especially where energy efficiency dominates over speed. 
 
